The Pine Bend Refinery covered process complies with OSHA Standard 29 CFR 1910.119, Process Safety Management of highly hazardous chemicals, and FHR has applied the programs and policies found in the standard to activities throughout the facility. Specific program elements include: 



Employee Participation ? It is the policy of Flint Hills Resources (FHR) to seek participation of employees at all levels in establishing procedures and practices that govern Health, Safety and Environmental issues. The Employee Participation Plan (SAF-5(3.0)007) includes a description of how the Employee Participation element is implemented; 



Process Safety Information ? Process safety information is maintained for the facility. The Process Safety Information Job Aid (SAF-5(3.0)001) includes a description of how the Process Safety Information element is implemented; 



Process Hazard Analysis ? A detailed process hazard assessment, using HAZOP and LOPA, is conducted on the facility to ensure that it has been designed safely. The Process Hazard Analysis Procedure (SAF-5(2.0)005) includes a description of how the Process Hazard Analysis element is implemented; 



Operating Procedures ? A system is in place to ensure that updated and approved procedures cover all aspects of the facility's operation. The Corporate FHR Operating Procedures Performance Standard includes a description of how the Operating Procedure element is to be implemented at Pine Bend; 



Training ? A training program has been established to ensure that personnel are well trained in the specific duties of their jobs. The Learning and Performance Team is responsible for training of operations personnel; 



Contractors ? It is FHR's objective to partner with contractors that share the same safety philosophy. A dedicated, collective, and consistent approach by FHR and contractors will enhance and maintain the safety and health of our respective employees. The Pine Bend Contractor Safety Program element is included in the Contractor Risk Management Policy (CON-2(1.0)003); 



Pre-startup Safety Review ? A pre-startup safety review walk down and checklist is completed for each managed change that significantly impacts the Process Safety Information. The Management of Change Procedure (SAF-5(2.0)001) includes a description of how the Pre-startup Safety Review element is implemented; 



Mechanical Integrity ? An equipment inspection program is in place to ensure equipment remains in good condition to prevent releases. The Mechanical Integrity element is implemented and documented in FHR Standards and multiple Mechanical Integrity procedures, refer to the Organizational chart for more information; 



Hot Work Permits ? A work permit system is in place to ensure that work on process equipment and all hot work are conducted in a safe manner. The Hot Work Procedure (SAF-2(2.0)010) includes a description of how the Hot Work element is implemented;



Management of Change ? A management of change system has been established and implemented to ensure that any change is thoroughly reviewed prior to implementation. The Management of Change Procedure (SAF-5(2.0)001) includes a description of how the Management of Change element is implemented; 



 Incident Investigation ? Incidents are investigated using one of several industry recognized methodologies, such as Cause Mapping or Root Cause Failure Analysis, to determine system level root causes that can be remedied to prevent a recurrence. Employees and contractors involved in the incident are included on the investigation team. The Pine Bend Organizational Learning Guidance Document (SAF-6(3.0)002) includes a description of how the Incident Investigation element is implemented; 



Emergency Planning and Response ? An emergency action plan has been established, and the site is part of the Community Emergency Response Plan. The site?s ICP ?One Plan? includes a description of how the Emergency Planning and Response element is implemented; 



Compliance Audits ? Programs are reviewed regularly and audited at least every three years through PSM compliance audits; and safety inspections of the facility are conducted by cross functional teams. The site works with Koch Audit Services and second and/or third party auditors to implement the Compliance Audit element;
